From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: David Allsopp <david.allsopp@metastack.com>
Date: Mon, 25 May 2026 12:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Regenerated configure script for relocatability features

The aNN patches update configure.ac with relocatability options
(--enable-runtime-search, --with-relative-libdir, etc.) but the
pre-generated configure script also needs to be updated.  OCaml's
build system uses the pre-generated configure directly without
re-running autoconf, so the new options are silently ignored without
this patch.

Patch a01 is a cherry-pick of dra27 base commit 5fe7f0fbcb which updates the
version string (4.14.3 -> 4.14.3+relocatable) in configure via a binary delta.
This patch (a90) covers all remaining configure changes from that base commit
to the final dra27 relocatable commit (8b8971e46f5c09aedb5f8d43a6e2701fecc8f98d).
Generating a90 from vanilla 4.14.3 would cause a conflict with a01's version
hunk, so a90 is based on the post-a01 (5fe7f0fbcb) state of configure.

Upstream: https://github.com/dra27/ocaml/commits/8b8971e46f5c09aedb5f8d43a6e2701fecc8f98d
